A vintage 1960s style illustration of a person trapped inside a rotary telephone, their frustrated face visible through the dial holes, surrounded by an endless tangle of coiled phone cords that spiral into a maze-like pattern. The color palette features muted mustard yellows, burnt oranges, and olive greens typical of mid-century design. The phone cords weave through the composition like a labyrinth, some cords leading to other smaller rotary phones floating in the background, creating a sense of endless transfers and loops. The person's expression shows exhaustion and exasperation. The overall aesthetic mimics vintage advertising posters with slightly grainy texture and bold geometric shapes.
